147749.name: fish_catch_direct_consumption
147749.description: Wild fish catch which is used for direct human consumption.
147749.datasetName: Global fish catch by end use (FishStat via SeaAroundUs)

source.name: FishStat via Pauly, Zeller, and Palomares from Sea Around Us Concepts, Design and Data.
source.dataPublishedBy: Pauly D., Zeller D., Palomares M.L.D. (Editors), 2020. Sea Around Us Concepts, Design and Data (seaaroundus.org).
source.additionalInfo:
This data is sourced from the Sea Around Us database published by Pauly, Zeller and Palomares, available at: http://www.seaaroundus.org/.

This project relies on multiple sources but primarily the FishStat database published by the Food and Agriculture Organization of the United Nations. This is available here: http://www.fao.org/fishery/statistics/software/fishstatj/en.

147750.name: fishmeal_and_fish_oil
147750.description: This is the quantity of wild fish catch that is used as fishmeal and fish oil for animal feed. This feed is used in land-based livestock farming (e.g. pigs, cows, chickens) and aquaculture (fish farming).
